items.title: Who is James Comey, the Trump critic and ex-FBI director who has just been indicted?
items.summary: James Comey, who was fired by Donald Trump during the US president's first term, has been charged with two criminal counts.

items.title: Palestinian leader condemns Israel's assault on Gaza, rejects Hamas during UN address
items.summary: Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas addressed the UN General Assembly via video, accusing Israel of war crimes and declaring that Hamas will have no future role in governing Gaza.

items.title: 'Unauthorised' edit of Australian film Together removes same-sex couple for audiences in China
items.summary: The film Together has reportedly been altered using artificial intelligence by a Chinese film distributor.

items.title: Donald Trump says any Israeli annexation of the West Bank is 'not going to happen'
items.summary: The US president has rejected calls from some members of the Israeli prime minister's coalition for Israel to fully annex the West Bank.

items.title: Key questions behind this controversial United Nations address
items.summary: He once led a designated terrorist group. Now, Syria's Ahmed al-Sharaa leads the country and has addressed the United Nations. But was his appearance there really another step in a "dramatic" political transformation?

items.title: Trump overcomes 'resistance' from China to transfer TikTok to US investors
items.summary: The US president said Rupert Murdoch, along with other "world-class investors", would be involved in the deal.

items.title: Former French President Nicolas Sarkozy jailed for five years over Libyan criminal conspiracy case
items.summary: Sarkozy, who has always denied the charges, was accused of making a deal with former Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi to obtain campaign financing.

items.title: 'Hybrid attack': Drones over Danish airports intended to spread fear, authorities say
items.summary: The incidents are just the latest in a series of drone incursions — including two days ago in Denmark — in the past few weeks that have exposed the vulnerability of European airspace.

items.title: 'Thanks for waking me up': Untold story behind Cathy Freeman's Olympic glory
items.summary: On the 25th anniversary of Cathy Freeman's 400m gold win at the Sydney Olympics, John-Paul Janke looks back at the time she stayed at his home in Canberra.

items.title: It's 'third time lucky' for an Alzheimer's drug. But many Australians like Peter will miss out
items.summary: Australia's medicines watchdog has approved Alzheimer's drug lecanemab, which has been shown to "significantly" extend quality of life. But it comes at a great cost.

items.title: When will humans return to the moon? NASA's new mission is offering clues
items.summary: The last time humans landed on the moon was in December 1972.

items.title: Albanese pushes for Security Council seat and calls out Iran in first major UN speech
items.summary: The UN risks "being trusted with nothing" unless it works together to tackle climate change and end wars in Gaza and Ukraine, Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has said during his first UN General Assembly address.

items.title: 'Treated like an afterthought': Phil often felt invisible during his family's IVF journey
items.summary: Years of IVF treatment saw Phil Ceberano and his wife Angela navigate not only the physical and emotional toll of repeated rounds, but also the silence and invisibility felt by male partners.

items.title: Greenlandic girls as young as 12 were forcibly fitted with IUDs. Denmark just apologised
items.summary: By the end of 1970, roughly every second Greenland-born woman of childbearing age had been fitted with an IUD.

items.title: Liberal Gisele Kapterian abandons court challenge and concedes defeat in Bradfield
items.summary: After 145 days, Liberal Gisele Kapterian has conceded defeat in the Sydney seat of Bradfield to her rival, independent MP Nicolette Boele.

items.title: Stop Russia's war or face dangerous arms race, Zelenskyy tells UN
items.summary: Volodymyr Zelenskyy also accused Vladimir Putin of seeking to expand his war beyond Ukraine.

items.title: This Christian community embraces traditional living. But ex-members allege it has dark secrets
items.summary: When Dateline journalist Rhiona-Jade Armont travelled to the US for a story about tradwives, she’d never heard of Homestead Heritage. She soon learned the Christian group had a dark history of abuse — and former members allege there’s more. But current members and leaders say it’s a sovereign sanctuary from the outside world.

items.title: Bathurst mum's plea at UN as Australia's social media ban lauded by world leaders
items.summary: Australian mother Emma Mason told the UN General Assembly that social media platforms "played their deadly part" in her daughter's death by suicide.

items.title: 'Anti-ICE' message found on unused bullet after fatal attack on Dallas immigration office
items.summary: US Homeland Security secretary Kristi Noem and vice president JD Vance condemned rhetoric directed at Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) since Donald Trump's return to office.

items.title: Greta Thunberg calls alleged drone attacks on aid flotilla a 'scare tactic' as UN demands probe
items.summary: The United Nations has called for an independent investigation into alleged drone attacks on the Global Sumud Flotilla, an international convoy carrying humanitarian aid to Gaza.

items.title: 'Warm chat' and a selfie: Albanese finally comes face-to-face with Trump
items.summary: Anthony Albanese has met Donald Trump at the president's welcome reception for world leaders in New York after the pair locked in a formal sit-down for October.

items.title: Three-year inflation high could mean 'wafer-thin' chance of interest rate cut pre November
items.summary: Freshly released inflation data will prompt the Reserve Bank to keep the cash rate on hold in September, but a cut in November is still "very much on the cards", experts say.

items.title: Optus to pay $100m fine for sales practices targeting vulnerable Australians
items.summary: Amid Optus' triple-zero outage crisis, the Federal Court has added to the company's woes after approving a $100 million penalty for "appalling and predatory" conduct in the telco's sales practices.

items.title: Super Typhoon Ragasa: Cyclone bears down on southern China after 17 killed in Taiwan
items.summary: Millions of people in southern China are in Typhoon Ragasa's sights after the most powerful cyclone of 2025 battered Hong Kong and killed 17 people in Taiwan.
